manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Shoe Organizer for Entryway 4-tier shoe rack is designed to provide you with a clean and orderly shoe storage solution. Made of high-quality materials, this shoe rack is strong and stable, and can withstand the weight of multiple pairs of shoes.

Shoe rack details MDF Board The top board can be used as a platform for other items, such as potted plants, photo frames or other decorative items. Anti-tipping webbing The shoe rack is equipped with two anti-toppling webbing, which can fix it to the wall and make it more stable when used. Metal shelves The shoe rack is made of high-quality metal, which is durable, easy to clean, and not easily filled with dust. Curved design The front two metal feet of the shoe rack are curved outward, more stable than the straight, and are not easy to tip forward.

Shoe Storage Our shoe rack design is simple and stylish, to suit a variety of interior decoration styles. Whether in the foyer, bedroom or cloakroom, it provides a neat storage space for your shoes. The distance between each shelf is high enough to accommodate various types of shoes, including sports shoes, high heels, boots, etc.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best Bang for the Bucks
reviews.reviewText: My wife and I read a LOT of reviews here for shoe racks. She wanted something for 20 pairs of her shoes. (Beware those racks using fabric; too many complaining about it ripping.) This rack had the slightly extended front legs for stability that no others have. It's all metal except for the two top boards. Everything went together nicely, only one screw that was harder to put in. It's strong, well braced, and ours didn't have to be tethered to the wall to prevent tip-over. (But we have no cats or little kiddies to pull it over.)This get a rare 5 star recommendation from me, and I'm pretty picky.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Holds a lot of shoes, easy to assemble, good looking
reviews.reviewText: We are a "shoes off at the door" family and usually put our shoes in one of those flat cabinets with the doors that open at an angle. The problem is that the angled drawers don't hold that many shoes and it was getting really messy around the cabinet with extra shoes piling up. This shoe organizer is perfect for our entryway. It is really easy to assemble, there is enough shelf space for everyone's shoes to get put away neatly, and the wood top is great to have catch-all bins for everyone's small items. The only critique I have is that there is a little bit of a wobble since the shelves are wire metal, but it still is nothing that detracts from the look and quality. I did not use the little wall straps either so that's on me. Overall, I am really happy with the amount of shoes this holds and how nice it looks at the entryway.
